<item>
            <title>[LU-1498] Test failure on replay-single.sh test_31 &quot;post-failover df: 254&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1498</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1cb6e14a-b126-11e1-ae39-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1cb6e14a-b126-11e1-ae39-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_31 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;replay-single test_31: @@@@@@ FAIL: post-failover df: 254&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Typical test runs look like the following on the MDS:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18:43:15:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: == replay-single test 31: open(O_CREAT) two, unlink one, |X| unlink one, close two (test mds_cleanup_orphans) ====================================================================================================== 15:43:13 (1338936193)&lt;br/&gt;
18:43:17:Turning device dm-0 (0xfd00000) read-only&lt;br/&gt;
18:43:18:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: mds1 REPLAY BARRIER on lustre-MDT0000&lt;br/&gt;
18:43:23:Removing read-only on unknown block (0xfd00000)&lt;br/&gt;
18:43:34:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): 6 orphan inodes deleted&lt;br/&gt;
18:43:34:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): recovery complete&lt;br/&gt;
18:43:35:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): mounted filesystem with ordered data mode. Opts: &lt;br/&gt;
18:43:35:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): mounted filesystem with ordered data mode. Opts: &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but on the failed run there were some extra &quot;osd_ro()&quot; messages:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;19:59:22:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: == replay-single test 31: open(O_CREAT) two, unlink one, |X| unlink one, close two (test mds_cleanup_orphans) ====================================================================================================== 16:59:21 (1338940761)&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:25:LustreError: 22034:0:(osd_handler.c:1003:osd_ro()) *** setting device osd-ldiskfs read-only ***&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:26:LustreError: 22034:0:(osd_handler.c:1003:osd_ro()) Skipped 22 previous similar messages&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:26:Turning device dm-0 (0xfd00000) read-only&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:26:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: mds1 REPLAY BARRIER on lustre-MDT0000&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:32:Removing read-only on unknown block (0xfd00000)&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:43:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): 5 orphan inodes deleted&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:43:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): recovery complete&lt;br/&gt;
19:59:43:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): mounted filesystem with ordered data mode. Opts: &lt;br/&gt;
19:59:43:LDISKFS-fs (dm-0): mounted filesystem with ordered data mode. Opts: &lt;br/&gt;
19:59:48:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: replay-single test_31: @@@@@@ FAIL: post-failover df: 254&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: replay-single 31&lt;/p&gt;</description>
